---
hvy_version: 0.1
title: Job Search Workspace
reader_max_width: 64rem
section_defaults:
  css: "margin: 0.5rem 0;"
plugins:
  - id: dev.heavy.db-table
    source: builtin://db-table
  - id: dev.heavy.form
    source: builtin://form
  - id: dev.heavy.progress-bar
    source: builtin://progress-bar
  - id: dev.heavy.scripting
    source: builtin://scripting
---

<!--hvy: {"id":"overview"}-->
#! Overview

<!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
This default HVY document is a lightweight workspace for tracking a job search. It mixes narrative sections with a SQLite-backed plugin block whose rows are expected to come from the attached database.

<!--hvy:quote {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
Keep the visible document focused on the next decision, and let the attached data hold the larger working set.

<!--hvy:grid {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","gridColumns":2}-->

 <!--hvy:grid:0 {"id":"goal"}-->

  <!--hvy:container {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->

   <!--hvy:container:0 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     ## Current Goal

   <!--hvy:container:1 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     Land three strong interviews this month without losing track of follow-ups.

 <!--hvy:grid:1 {"id":"focus"}-->

  <!--hvy:container {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->

   <!--hvy:container:0 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     ## Focus This Week

   <!--hvy:container:1 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     - [x] Refresh portfolio links
     - [ ] Send two recruiter follow-ups
     - [ ] Tailor resume for platform roles

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"application-pipeline","highlight":true}-->
#! Application Pipeline

<!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
Use the plugin block below as the working application table. The rendered rows should come from the attached SQLite file rather than from inline HVY table data.

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.db-table","pluginConfig":{"source":"with-file","table":"job_applications"}}-->

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"notes"}-->
#! Notes

<!--hvy:expandable {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","expandableAlwaysShowStub":true,"expandableExpanded":false}-->

 <!--hvy:expandable:stub {}-->

  <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
   Strong leads worth extra prep

 <!--hvy:expandable:content {}-->

  <!--hvy:container {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->

   <!--hvy:container:0 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     Northwind Labs and Lattice Systems are both good fits for reusable systems work, documentation-heavy delivery, and platform ownership.

   <!--hvy:container:1 {}-->

    <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
     Prepare stories around migration planning, developer tooling, and AI-assisted workflows before the next calls.

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"next-steps"}-->
#! Next Steps

<!--hvy:component-list {"componentListComponent":"text","css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->

 <!--hvy:component-list:0 {}-->

  <!--hvy:text {}-->
   Ask for feedback from roles that have stalled for more than 10 days.

 <!--hvy:component-list:1 {}-->

  <!--hvy:text {}-->
   Split opportunities into "must pursue" and "nice to pursue" before adding more applications.

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.db-table"}-->

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"progress-bar-example"}-->
#! Progress Bar Example

<!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
The block below is a simple themed progress bar example that should pick up the active accent color by default.

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.progress-bar","pluginConfig":{"min":0,"max":100,"value":68}}-->
${value}%

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"scripting-example"}-->
#! Scripting Example

<!--hvy:text {"id":"script-value","css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
Script test value: 0

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.scripting","pluginConfig":{"version":"0.1"}}-->
doc.header.set("last_viewed", "from python!")

output = doc.tool("view_component", {"component_ref": "script-value"})
for line in output.split('\n'):
    if "Script test value:" in line:
        parts = line.split('|', 1)
        if len(parts) == 2:
            line_no = int(parts[0].strip())
            curr_val = int(parts[1].split('Script test value:')[1].strip())
            doc.tool("patch_component", {
                "component_ref": "script-value",
                "edits": [{
                    "op": "replace",
                    "start_line": line_no,
                    "end_line": line_no,
                    "text": f"Script test value: {curr_val + 1}"
                }]
            })
        break


<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"form-examples"}-->
#! Form Examples

<!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
These form plugin blocks keep their input definitions in YAML text owned by `dev.heavy.form`. They exercise static options, script-populated fields, field triggers, submit handling, and the core HTML input types without introducing standalone HVY input components.

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.form","pluginConfig":{"version":"0.1","initialScript":"populate_lunch","submitScript":"submit_lunch","submitLabel":"Save lunch order"}}-->
fields:
  - label: Lunch choice
    type: select
    value: soup
    required: true
    options:
      - label: Sandwich
        value: sandwich
      - label: Soup
        value: soup
      - label: Salad
        value: salad
    triggers:
      change: populate_lunch
  - label: Suggested side
    type: text
    placeholder: Pick a food first
  - label: Delivery date
    type: date
  - label: Notes
    type: textarea
    placeholder: Allergies, timing, or other details
  - label: Rush order
    type: checkbox
    value: false
scripts:
  populate_lunch: |
    food = doc.form.get_value("Lunch choice")
    sides = {
        "sandwich": "Kettle chips",
        "soup": "Sourdough roll",
        "salad": "Iced tea",
    }
    doc.form.set_value("Suggested side", sides.get(food, ""))
  submit_lunch: |
    values = doc.form.get_values()
    if not values.get("Delivery date"):
        doc.form.set_error("Delivery date", "Choose a delivery date before submitting.")
    else:
        doc.form.clear_error("Delivery date")
        doc.header.set("last_lunch_order", values)

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.form","pluginConfig":{"version":"0.1","initialScript":"update_summary","submitScript":"submit_contact","showSubmit":false}}-->
fields:
  - label: Full name
    type: text
    placeholder: Ada Lovelace
    required: true
  - label: Email
    type: email
    placeholder: ada@example.com
  - label: Phone
    type: tel
    placeholder: 555-0100
  - label: Portfolio URL
    type: url
    placeholder: https://example.com
  - label: Access phrase
    type: password
  - label: Interview count
    type: number
    value: "3"
    triggers:
      input: update_summary
  - label: Preferred contact
    type: radio
    value: email
    options:
      - label: Email
        value: email
      - label: Phone
        value: phone
      - label: Portfolio review
        value: portfolio
    triggers:
      change: update_summary
  - label: Summary
    type: textarea
    meta:
      css: "min-height: 4rem;"
  - label: Source
    type: hidden
    value: example-document
scripts:
  update_summary: |
    count = doc.form.get_value("Interview count") or "0"
    method = doc.form.get_value("Preferred contact") or "email"
    doc.form.set_value("Summary", f"Plan for {count} interview touchpoint(s), follow up by {method}.")
  submit_contact: |
    values = doc.form.get_values()
    if not values.get("Full name"):
        doc.form.set_error("Full name", "Name is required.")
    else:
        doc.form.clear_error("Full name")
        doc.header.set("last_contact_form", values)

<!--hvy:subsection {"id":"import-failure-example"}-->
#! Import Failure Example

<!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
The script below intentionally attempts to import `browser.window` so you can inspect what the current scripting environment allows and how failure is surfaced if that import path is blocked.

<!--hvy:text {"id":"import-example-result","css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;"}-->
Import example result: pending

<!--hvy:plugin {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0;","plugin":"dev.heavy.scripting","pluginConfig":{"version":"0.1"}}-->
from browser import window

output = doc.tool("view_component", {"component_ref": "import-example-result"})
for line in output.split('\n'):
    if "Import example result:" in line:
        parts = line.split('|', 1)
        if len(parts) == 2:
            line_no = int(parts[0].strip())
            doc.tool("patch_component", {
                "component_ref": "import-example-result",
                "edits": [{
                    "op": "replace",
                    "start_line": line_no,
                    "end_line": line_no,
                    "text": f"Import example result: browser import worked ({window.location.href})"
                }]
            })
        break
<!--hvy:tail {"plugin":"dev.heavy.scripting","mediaType":"application/vnd.sqlite3","encoding":"gzip"}-->
